            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Gas Stoves</h3>
              <p>
                Gas stoves are popular for their precise temperature control and
                quick heat adjustments, making them a favorite among many home
                cooks and professional chefs. However, they come with their own
                set of repair needs. Common issues include faulty igniters,
                which can prevent the burners from lighting, and clogged burner
                ports, which can result in uneven flames or no flame at all. Gas
                leaks are another serious concern, often identified by a
                distinct smell of gas—this issue requires immediate professional
                attention to ensure safety. Other potential problems include
                malfunctioning thermostats in the oven and issues with the gas
                supply line. Regular maintenance, such as cleaning the burners
                and checking for gas leaks, can help mitigate some of these
                issues, but professional repairs are often necessary to handle
                more complex problems safely.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Electric Stoves</h3>
              <p>
                Electric stoves are known for their ease of use and consistent
                heating, but they are not without their repair needs. Common
                problems include malfunctioning heating elements, which can
                result in burners that don’t heat up or heat unevenly. The oven
                element may also wear out, causing the oven to fail to reach the
                desired temperature. Issues with the stove’s wiring or control
                board can lead to problems with temperature regulation and
                overall functionality. Diagnosing electrical issues can be
                complicated and potentially dangerous, so it’s often best to
                call in a professional technician. Regularly cleaning the
                stovetop and ensuring that the burners and oven are free from
                debris can help prolong the life of your electric stove.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
