                cooking, offering a gas cooktop for precise temperature control
                and an electric oven for even baking. While these stoves provide
                versatility, they also come with a broader range of potential
                repair needs. Issues can arise in both the gas and electric
                components, such as faulty igniters, malfunctioning heating
                elements, or problems with the dual-fuel interface.
                Additionally, the complexity of dual-fuel stoves means that
                troubleshooting and repairs can be more complicated compared to
                single-fuel models. Regular maintenance is essential to keep
                both the gas and electric parts working efficiently. Given their
                complexity, professional repair services are often required to
                address any significant issues, ensuring both components
                function harmoniously.
              </p>
