                <div class="questions">
                  <p>
                    If your dryer is making a loud noise, it can be quite
                    concerning. Here are some common reasons why this could be
                    happening and what you can do about it:
                  </p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <b>Foreign Objects: </b>Sometimes, items can get caught in
                      the drum or the lint trap. Check for objects like coins,
                      buttons, or small toys that might have been left in
                      pockets and made their way into the dryer. Just like you
                      would check a washer for stray items before starting a
                      load, make sure to inspect the dryer as well.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Worn Drum Rollers: </b>The drum rollers support the
                      drum as it rotates. Over time, these can wear out and
                      cause a loud rumbling noise. If you suspect this is the
                      issue, you might need to replace the rollers. This is a
                      bit more involved and could require opening up the
                      machine.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Damaged Drive Belt: </b>The drive belt helps the drum
                      to turn. If it's worn or damaged, it can make a thumping
                      or squealing noise. To check, you may need to unplug the
                      dryer and look inside the back panel. If the belt is
                      frayed or broken, it will need to be replaced.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Faulty Motor: </b>The motor is what powers the drum to
                      spin. If it's faulty, it can make a loud humming or
                      grinding noise. This could be a more complex issue and
                      might require professional attention.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Imbalanced Load: </b>Just like with washers, an
                      imbalanced load in your dryer can cause it to make a lot
                      of noise. Make sure that the items are evenly distributed
                      in the drum. Large, heavy items like blankets or towels
                      can sometimes cause this issue.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Loose Parts: </b>Over time, various parts of the dryer
                      can become loose. Check the drum paddles, screws, and
                      other components to ensure everything is tight and secure.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Blower Wheel: </b>The blower wheel helps to circulate
                      air through the dryer. If it's damaged or obstructed, it
                      can make a loud noise. You might need to open the machine
                      to check and clean or replace the blower wheel.
                    </li>
